Ansible

1. Install and configure Ansible, Puppet, or Chef on a local or cloud
environment. Write and execute basic configuration scripts.?


Step 1: Install Ansible
# For Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ansible -y

# For CentOS/RHEL
sudo yum install epel-release -y
sudo yum install ansible -y

Step 2: Inventory Setup
Edit or create the Ansible inventory file:

sudo vi /etc/ansible/hosts

ADD

[webservers]
localhost ansible_connection=local


Step 3: Basic Playbook
Create a playbook named install_apache.yml:

---
- name: Install and start Apache
  hosts: webservers
  become: true
  tasks:
    - name: Install Apache
      apt:
        name: apache2
        state: present
      when: ansible_os_family == "Debian"

    - name: Start Apache service
      service:
        name: apache2
        state: started
        enabled: yes

RUN Playbook

ansible-playbook install_apache.yml


Puppet install

Debian/Ubuntu -->

wget https://apt.puppetlabs.com/puppet-release-focal.deb
sudo dpkg -i puppet-release-focal.deb
sudo apt update
sudo apt install puppet-agent -y


Chef install

# Download Chef Workstation from https://www.chef.io/downloads/tools/workstation
Debian:
wget https://packages.chef.io/files/stable/chef-workstation/XX/ubuntu/20.04/chef-workstation_XX_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i chef-workstation_XX_amd64.deb
